# Workflow Guidelines - Orbito Platform

## Development Workflow

### Task Approach

1. Read task requirements completely
2. Check existing code for patterns
3. Install dependencies first
4. Implement incrementally
5. Test after each step
6. Commit working code frequently

### AI-Assisted Coding

- Provide complete context upfront
- Break complex tasks into steps
- Specify exact file paths
- Include error messages fully
- State what was already tried
- Ask for clarification if unclear

### Code Review Process

- Self-review before submission
- Check for security issues
- Verify business logic
- Ensure consistent style
- Add necessary comments
- Update related documentation

## Git Conventions

### Branch Strategy

- main: production-ready
- develop: integration branch
- feature/[task-name]: new features
- fix/[issue-name]: bug fixes
- hotfix/[issue]: urgent production fixes

### Commit Messages

- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- refactor: code restructuring
- docs: documentation updates
- test: test additions/changes
- chore: maintenance tasks

### Pull Requests

- Link to issue/task
- Describe changes clearly
- Include testing steps
- Add screenshots for UI
- Request specific reviewers
- Resolve conflicts locally

## Naming Conventions

### Backend

- PascalCase: Classes, Methods, Properties
- camelCase: variables, parameters
- UPPERCASE: constants
- Prefix interfaces with I
- Suffix handlers with Handler
- Suffix validators with Validator

### Frontend

- PascalCase: Components, Types
- camelCase: functions, variables
- kebab-case: file names
- UPPERCASE: constants
- use prefix for hooks
- Props suffix for prop types

### Database

- PascalCase: Table names
- PascalCase: Column names
- IX\_: Index prefix
- FK\_: Foreign key prefix
- UK\_: Unique constraint prefix
- CK\_: Check constraint prefix

## Documentation Standards

### Code Comments

- Explain why, not what
- Document complex algorithms
- Note important decisions
- Add TODO with assignee
- Reference issue numbers
- Keep comments updated

### API Documentation

- Document all endpoints
- Include request/response examples
- Specify error codes
- Note authentication requirements
- Document rate limits
- Version changes clearly

### README Files

- Project overview first
- Setup instructions
- Environment variables
- Common issues/solutions
- Development guidelines
- Contact information

## Error Handling

### Backend Errors

- Use Result<T> pattern
- Return specific error codes
- Log with correlation ID
- Include helpful messages
- Don't expose internals
- Handle gracefully

### Frontend Errors

- Show user-friendly messages
- Log to console in development
- Provide retry options
- Handle network failures
- Show loading states
- Fallback UI for crashes

## Testing Workflow

### Before Implementation

- Understand requirements
- Plan test scenarios
- Consider edge cases
- Identify dependencies

### During Implementation

- Write tests alongside code
- Run tests frequently
- Fix failures immediately
- Refactor with confidence

### After Implementation

- Run full test suite
- Check code coverage
- Test manually
- Verify in different environments

## Communication Patterns

### With AI Assistants

- Start fresh session if stuck
- Provide complete file contents
- Include exact error messages
- State attempted solutions
- Ask for specific approaches
- Confirm understanding

### With Team

- Daily standup updates
- Blocker communication ASAP
- Document decisions
- Share learnings
- Review PRs promptly
- Provide constructive feedback

## Quality Checklist

### Before Starting

- [ ] Requirements clear
- [ ] Dependencies identified
- [ ] Approach planned
- [ ] Existing patterns reviewed

### During Development

- [ ] Following conventions
- [ ] Tests written
- [ ] Error handling added
- [ ] Security considered
- [ ] Performance checked

### Before Submission

- [ ] Code self-reviewed
- [ ] Tests passing
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] No console.logs
- [ ] No commented code
- [ ] Migrations tested

## Debugging Strategy

### Systematic Approach

1. Reproduce consistently
2. Isolate the problem
3. Check recent changes
4. Review error messages
5. Add logging
6. Test hypothesis
7. Fix root cause

### When Stuck

- Take a break
- Start fresh session
- Ask for different approach
- Check documentation
- Review similar code
- Pair program
- Break into smaller parts

## Performance Monitoring

### Key Metrics

- Response time <200ms
- Error rate <1%
- Database query time
- Memory usage
- CPU utilization
- Concurrent users

### Optimization Priority

1. Database queries
2. External API calls
3. Algorithm efficiency
4. Caching strategy
5. Bundle size
6. Image optimization
